                  <summary><p>This manuscript of the <title xml:lang="sa">Vṛddhahārītasmṛti</title> is the third in a collection of five <term xml:lang="sa">smṛti</term> texts. The scribe has left empty spaces, sometimes filled with dots, which seem to represent illegible or damaged spans of texts in the antigraph that he was copying from. This manuscript breaks off at verse 330 of the sixth <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term> (ed. Shastri et al., <ref target="https://archive.org/details/smriti-sandarbha-gurumandal-series/Smriti%20Sandarbha%20Part%202%20-%20Gurumandal%20Series%201952/page/n618/mode/1up">1159</ref>), although it is not clear whether there are missing folios at the end.</p>
</summary>
                  
               <msItem defective="true"><title xml:lang="sa">Vṛddhahārītasmṛti</title><textLang mainLang="san"/><rubric xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="1r" facs="73" unit="folio"/>yasya dvirada vaktrādyāḥ pāriṣadyaḥ paraś śataṃ | vighnan nighnanti satataṃ viṣvakṣenan tamāśraye | hariḥ om |</rubric><incipit xml:lang="sa">aṃbarīṣas tu taṃ gatvā hārītasyāśramaṃ nṛpaṃ | ....nde taṃ mahātmānaṃ bālārkasadṛśaprabhaṃ |</incipit><explicit xml:lang="sa"><milestone facs="126" n="50v" unit="folio"/>matipūrvveṇa gāṃ hatvā cari<unclear>kṣyā</unclear>vārṣikaṃ vrataṃ |</explicit></msItem></msContents>
